criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Rheumatoid arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis, hemophilia sex arthritis, gouty arthritis;
2. acute knee joint infection, or systemic infection;
3. Within 1 week of oral antiplatelet or against the use of fibrinolytic drugs, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs or corticosteroids and immunosuppressive drugs;
4. Knee joint cavity injected drugs within three months;
5. underwent knee related to surgery within half year;
6. has blood system diseases, cardiovascular disease, diabetes, immune deficiency diseases,tumor and so on;
7. hemoglobin is less than 11 g/dL, platelet count is less than 100*10^9/L  white blood cell count is less than 3*10^9/L
